olive oil
1.25 cup water
1 packet jasmine rice
1 bunch spring onion
1 packet teriyaki sauce
3.5 tsp brown sugar
1 tbs soy sauce
1 tsp sesame oil
1 packet mayonnaise
½ sachet mixed sesame seeds
1 packet garlic paste
1 packet beef strips
1 tsp vinegar (rice wine or white wine)
1 bag Asian Stir-Fry Mix

• Add the water to a medium saucepan, then bring to the boil.
• Add jasmine rice, stir, cover with a lid and reduce heat to low.
• Cook for 12 minutes, then remove pan from heat and keep covered until rice is tender and water is absorbed, 10-15 minutes.

TIP: The rice will finish cooking in its own steam so don't peek!

• Meanwhile, thinly slice spring onion.
• In a small bowl, combine teriyaki sauce, the brown sugar, vinegar, soy sauce and half the sesame oil. Set aside.
• In a second small bowl, combine mayonnaise and remaining sesame oil. Set aside.
• Discard any liquid from beef strips packaging.

Little cooks: Kids can take charge by combining the sauces!

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over high heat. Cook When oil is hot, cook beef strips in batches, tossing, until browned and cooked through, 1-2 minutes. Return all beef to the pan
• Add Asian stir-fry mix, stirring, until softened, 2-3 minutes.
• Add garlic paste and mixed sesame seeds (see ingredients) and cook until fragrant, 1 minute.
• Add the teriyaki sauce mixture and stir until beef is coated, 1-2 minutes.

• Divide jasmine rice between bowls. Top with Japanese-style beef and veggie stir-fry.
• Dollop with sesame mayo. Garnish with spring onion to serve. Enjoy!

Little cooks: Add the finishing touch by sprinkling over the spring onion!